Johannesburg City Power JOHANNESBURG - City Power says it could take at least seven days to repair tripped transformers at the Eldorado Park substation, in southern Johannesburg. One transformer was stitched on Wednesday but tripped causing a blow-up on the second one. READ: Power cuts to downgrade to stage 3 from 10pm tonight City Power says if all goes according to plan, everything should be back to normal by early next week. Meanwhile, power cuts will be downgraded to stage 3 from 10pm on Wednesday. Eskom says six generating units have returned to service over the past 24 hours.